WorkItem.Description:
When you draw a selection rectangle, then context menus stop working. I think the reason is in this block (BorderSElectionLogic.cs):

internal override void OnMouseUp(MouseButtonEventArgs e)
{
...
        if (border != null)
       {
                border.Visibility = Visibility.Collapsed;
                border.Dispose();
                e.Handled = true;
        }
since border is never set back to null, the mouse up event will always be handled, thus context menus do not appear. I think a border = null should be inserted here, and also into "HandleInput"
